<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>Actually large generators normally do use electromagnets today.  They need an external source of power when starting, but drain off a very small part of the generated power to keep running.  As jacques wrote, that isn't done with small generators because the added complexity usually isn't worth it.</font></span><p><font size=1><font color=#f6f6ef>-----</font></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=120></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3375738 href="vote?for=3375738&dir=up&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%77%6c%36%53%64%38%32%6c%6f%5a"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3375738></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=mahyarm">mahyarm</a> 46 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3375738">link</a></span></div><br>
